[10]The ALFA 24 HP was presented on June 24, 1910.
[11]It had an engine designed by G. Merosi with a capacity of 4.084 cm3 developing an extraordinary power of 42 Hp, which allowed him to reach without difficulty the terrific speed of 100 km/h.
[12]The car was a huge success, in the first year alone it sold 50 copies.
